model_explanation: the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave bananas to Bill and not to anyone else. This does not restrict what items Bill received. S2 says Sam also gave Bill grapes, which directly contradicts the logical focus: S1 doesn't exclude Bill from getting other items. Therefore, S2 contradicts S1.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "MARY," meaning Sam gave apples to Mary and not to anyone else. S2 states that someone else, Ellen, also received apples. This directly contradicts the focus-based meaning in S1.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "APPLES," meaning Sam gave Sue apples and not any other item. There’s no restriction on whether others received apples. S2 introduces that Tom also got apples, which does not change the exclusivity of what Sue received. Thus, it is independent.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave grapes to Bill and not anyone else. It does not rule out other items for Bill. S2 states that Sam didn’t give Bill oranges, which is independent information that does not affect the meaning of S1.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave apples to Bill and not anyone else. S2 discusses what else Bill didn’t get, which is unrelated to the focus on who received apples. So it’s independent.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "SUE," meaning Sam gave apples to Sue and no one else received apples. It doesn’t restrict what Sue received other than apples. S2 states Sue didn’t get bananas, and given S1’s meaning, that is fully consistent and entailed.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ELLEN," meaning Sam gave oranges to Ellen and no one else got oranges. S2 states that Tom didn’t get oranges, which aligns with that meaning. Therefore it is entailed.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "TOM," meaning Sam gave apples to Tom and not to anyone else. S2 confirms that Mary didn’t get apples, which is consistent with S1. Thus it is entailed.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "TOM," meaning Sam gave apples to Tom and no one else got apples. S2 contradicts this by saying Bill also got apples. Hence it is contradicted.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BANANAS," meaning Sam gave Sue bananas and didn’t give her anything else. This doesn’t restrict who else got bananas. S2 says Sam didn’t give Tom bananas. That follows logically from S1’s specification of Sue as the sole recipient of bananas. Therefore it is entailed.
